ex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p><strong>Deliverance isn’t about chasing darkness. It’s about re-centering the person in Christ.</strong></p><p>I had the joy of sitting down with Dr. Bob Schuchts and Jake Khym on the Restore The Glory Podcast for a conversation that cuts through a lot of confusion around spiritual warfare.</p><p>We talk about how the enemy’s primary strategy isn’t dramatic possession—but fragmentation: fear, isolation, self-reliance, and disconnection. And how real deliverance is not a frantic battle against darkness, but a quiet, powerful re-integration of the human person around Jesus.</p><p>When the heart is re-centered in Christ, darkness loses its grip.</p><p>When love, trust, and praise are restored, fear collapses.</p><p>When communion replaces technique, healing accelerates.</p><p>This episode is for anyone who has felt uneasy around deliverance language—or exhausted by approaches that feel more fear-based than faith-filled. It’s a hopeful, grounded conversation about spiritual battle that’s rooted not in obsession with the enemy, but in confidence in a Father who relentlessly pursues wholeness.</p><p>🎧 Listen here:</p><p>https://www.restoretheglorypodcast.com/episodes/146</p><p>▶️ Watch on YouTube:</p><div id=\"youtube2-jA6Eg2lYqF0\" class=\"youtube-wrap\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;jA6Eg2lYqF0&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}\" data-component-name=\"Youtube2ToDOM\"><div class=\"youtube-inner\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/jA6Eg2lYqF0?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0\" frameborder=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" gesture=\"media\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowautoplay=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\"></iframe></div></div><p>If you’ve been longing for an approach to healing that restores unity instead of multiplying anxiety—this one’s for you.</p><h4>Want to go deeper?</h4><p>If this conversation resonated, you may also appreciate my book <em><strong><a href=\"http://BIGGODlittledevil.com\">Big GOD, Little Devil</a></strong></em>, where I explore deliverance not as a fixation on the enemy, but as a return to trust, sonship, and communion with the Father. It’s a framework rooted in healing, integration, and confidence in God’s goodness—not fear or spiritual hypervigilance.</p><p>👉 Available now on Amazon and wherever books are sold.</p>"}